						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the Kēśvasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>Pramādi.</p>						

						<p>(15th century A.D.)</p>						

						<p>This mutilated record can be assigned to 15th century A.D. on the basis of paleography though it mentions the cyclic year. Pramādi and Chaitra, śu.</p>						

						<p>Badly damaged and seems to record an <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> called Śrīraṅgapura.</p>						

						</summary>
